```php
<?php

// Function to calculate the sum of numbers from 1 to n using recursion.
function sumToN($n) {
    if ($n == 1) {
        return $n;
    } else {
        return $n + sumToN($n - 1);
    }
}
```

This function uses recursion to calculate the sum of numbers from 1 to n. It takes a number as input and returns the sum of numbers from 1 to that number. If the input is 1, it simply returns 1. Otherwise, it adds the current number to the result of calling the function with the previous number (n - 1). This process continues until the base case is reached (when n == 1), at which point the recursion stops and the sum is returned.

